title: an honest dialogue (mostly) & a makeup tutorial (kind of)
description:
when i sat down to film this makeup look, this is how i felt, so i wanted to be honest about it. 

please know that i appreciate you guys to the moon, but sometimes the negativity just crushes all the positivity, especially when struggling with mental health issues. 

when i‚Äôm not posting on youtube, i‚Äôm dealing with chronic fatigue, chronic illness, chronic pain, anxiety & depression & not a lot of motivation. hands up if u can relate! i have ehlers danlos syndrome, & it can be blamed for a lot of the above. 

i‚Äôm sorry to disappoint so many of you, but making content is not as important as trying to manage my physical & mental health, & it shouldn‚Äôt be!

to you sweet & patient angels, i love you.

hopefully someday i can be a regular content kind of creator.

xo

jordi

title: haunted daycare escape room vlog | scary challenge
description:
do you think we made it out in time? vote in the comments!

watch us (@caitmarks, @chanberry , @mikeycortez & i) try to get out of this horror themed escape room & save the souls of little girls, before we are trapped forever.
thank you escape hotel in hollywood for letting us bring a camera in! 

this was scary & amazing & i would go back in a heartbeat. we had 60 minutes to complete all the puzzles. each detail was perfect & well thought out. the vibe was totally creepy. one of my favourite nights ever!

have you ever been in an escape room? do you want to? 10/10 recommend.

title: the magic of makeup / FACE AWARDS 2017 final video/ nyx professional makeup
description:
nyx professional makeup FACE AWARDS final video. theme: "the magic of makeup" 

first of all- THANK YOU GUYS SO MUCH for voting me into the top 6 of the FACE AWARDS & giving me this radical opportunity. working with a crew (thank you to everyone who helped with the set, filming, lighting, editing..) was insane. so was 2 weeks of LA partying. i'm STILL tired. 

my concept:

there is a kind of magic that can reveal & glamorize all of your multiple personalities. 

this witchcraft can cure feelings of sadness & boredom & help you come out from hiding.

it has the power to express who you are,
& conjure your darkness while somehow letting your light shine at the same time

sorcery that embraces your morbid side, (flashback to show dark creature & your angelic side

the magic of makeup

it's okay to use this magic for darkness 
or for what you behold as beauty

the magic of makeup can do no harm

makeup is magic, & you can be the magician

only downside (for me) i like full coverage, & these bottles are small. 
i use probably 20-26 drops for a full face.
i could see these running out pretty fast!
